The paper focuses on compressive sensing and deep learning-based compressive sensing, which are both related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions image reconstruction, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions measurement matrices, which are related to matrix theory (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a method for simulating measurement loss, which could fall under signal processing (cs.SI).
